The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Hero Honda net profit grows 7.9%

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Jan 13: Hero Honda Motors, the country?s biggest motorcycle maker, today reported a 7.88 per cent rise in net profit for the third quarter of the current fiscal on the back of robust motorcycle sales.

 Net profit rose to Rs 219 crore during the October-December period over Rs 203 crore in the year-ago period, a company statement said.

 Net sales grew 25.6 per cent to Rs 2,043 crore during the quarter ended on December 31, over Rs 1,626 crore during the same period of the previous year.

 Hero Honda, in which Honda Motor Corp of Japan and the Munjals each hold 26 per cent stake, sold 24.4 per cent more motorcycles at 7,12,062 units during the third quarter of 2004-05 against 5,72,196 units in the year-ago period.

 Net profit for the first nine months recorded a rise of 16.6 per cent at Rs 603 crore over Rs 517 crore during the April-December period of 2003.

 Total turnover also jumped 30.7 per cent at Rs 5,587 crore against Rs 4,273 crore.

 ?This is the fourth year in a row that Hero Honda has maintained its position as the world?s no. 1 two-wheeler company...With enduring support from Honda, we will continue to lead the way and provide the best to our customers,? Hero Honda chairman Brijmohan Lall said. 

 Hero Honda has a 52 per cent share of India?s near 5 million bikes-a-year market.




